<br>
And as for the Yelinak thing, all I can say is...Verant REALLY doesnt want people fighting their dragons (and, of course, the obligatory they are fucking morons comment which should preface an explanation of anything they said or did in the past 6 months). After doing some rough calculations last night (based up damage our tanks took and some uninterrupted DA tanking) I came up with the following numbers;<br>
<br>
Average Yelinak Damage per Attack: 450<br>
Average Attacks Delivered per Tick: 16<br>
Average Yelinak Damage per Second: 1200<br>
<br>
Lets assume a warrior has the full attention of a mob. Without defensive up, a warrior with 6500 hp (assuming best hp/runes possible) can survive for 5.42 seconds. With defensive up (if it is indeed a 50 percent reduction in damage taken), the warrior can survive for 10.83 seconds.<br>
<br>
This will change over the course of a battle. Once the runes wear off, the best HP you can have is ~6000. If you have 4 clerics CHing you on 2.5s intervals, you are going to have your cleric pool aggro at 800 aggro points per second. There is no way any warrior can out-taunt this. Assuming a warrior FA proc every strike (which adds 500 to the warrior aggro), you can out-taunt (on average) the effect of clerics healing you when you increase your personal number of clerics to 7.<br>
(Note: If defensive was up, you only need 4 clerics to keep you alive, but they gain aggro faster than you can suck it back to you)<br>
<br>
Please note that this is a simple model to illustrate his current difficulty. The effects of damage and aggro from the other people in the battle take some of the heat off the warriors.<br>
<br>
Posted this here for visibility. Feel free to flame me or check my numbers, Im happy to edit my model in any way which makes it better (without having to break out paper hehe)<br>
<br>
Xarn Yum Chai<br>
