product that was relatively decent and fucked with it to the point where the majority of it's customer base was dissatisfied I would be shocked.  But this is VI we're talking about here.  Don't get me wrong, I'll be the first to admit that VI made one hell of a game.  Everquest is more than a game to most of us.  But I am beginning to think it was beginner's luck or something.  They have this golden product yet no fucking clue how it works or what to do with it.<br>
<br>
Let's talk specifically about the cleric hate AI.  Now picture for a minute that you aren't some fatass Verant employee sitting in San Diego masturbating to the art department's sketches of female dark elves (or male for that matter).  Instead you are a person who bought everquest to have fun. . for entertainment.  You chose to play CLERIC because that class appealed to you.  You find yourself in a guild that some might call *uber* which does very tough encounters requiring strategies beyong the average, "Press A" and hope for the best.  Up until this patch you were very good at your job.  Although it was near impossible, you found yourself often times able to save a tank from dying to a mob that quads for 800 or more.  Wondering whether that cheal was going to land in time was half the fun.  You were an essential part of the action.<br>
<br>
Then Verant NERFS you.  And they do it hard.<br>
<br>
Now this is what your average "big" encounter consists of.  Spending a massively tedious amount of time buffing people.  Sitting waiting for mana then casting more buffs.  Waiting for mana again.  Buffing.  Ok, now it's time to charge.  The mob you're charging quads for 800.  If a cheal doesn't land on your primary tank right away, he's dead.  If the primary tank dies too fast, most likely the whole raid will die through a dominoe effect.  So being a good cleric, you cast your cheal in order for it to save your tank thus saving your raid.  Lucky you!  Thanks to the new patch, you are now dead.<br>
<br>
The raid for you, Mr. Cleric, now consists of buffing people, charging and dying instantly.  It's so much fun to sit at home for the hours it takes to do an "epic encounter" reading guildchat, repeatedly asking, "are we gonna win? what's his health at?" because VI fucked with your class so hard you can't live long enough to HAVE FUN and DO YOUR JOB.<br>
<br>
Did Verant intend for clerics to be sacrificial lambs?  If so, awesome job guys.  Is the solution to get more clerics?  Well, who the fuck wants to play a class that's going die INSTANTLY every big raid for doing their job.  Are the new druid and shaman spells helping?  Helping get druids and shaman killed, yes.<br>
<br>
Are uber mobs now unkillable?  No, it's still possible.  But they are SUCKING THE FUN right out of it.  Was the Vision to have some person who has spent a lot of time building their cleric up to sit at home staring at the LOADING PLEASE WAIT dialogue?  Explain how this is fun or "more of a challenge".  It's fucking stupid is what it is.<br>
<br>
And nerfing clerics and warriors (the KEY, primary classes for all MAJOR encounters) will have a dominoe effect that reaches to all classes.  Way to rain on the parade, VI.  Bravo.<br>
<br>
Tigole Bitties<br>
Assassin of the Nameless<br>
Legacy of Steel</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=339&sid=77&pid=335&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#339">VI just invested into lots of Wolfpack studios stock.</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 16:29:16 EST</font><br><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=340&sid=77&pid=335&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#340">Re: Makes ya wonder</a> by Voronwe <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 16:29:21 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=342&sid=77&pid=340&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#342">Voronwe you silly silly ranger.</a> by Pilferr <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 16:39:10 EST</font><br><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=353&sid=77&pid=340&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#353">Re: Makes ya wonder</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 19:09:50 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=363&sid=77&pid=353&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#363">Re: Makes ya wonder</a> by Kreugen <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 22:16:57 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=381&sid=77&pid=363&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#381">WoR = death as well</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Friday, February 23 @ 09:02:25 EST</font><br><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=398&sid=77&pid=363&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#398">Re: Makes ya wonder</a> by Voronwe <font size=2>on Friday, February 23 @ 14:58:03 EST</font><br></ul></ul></ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=362&sid=77&pid=335&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#362">THIS is my biggest beef...</a> by Nino_FoH <font size=2>on Thursday, February 22 @ 21:31:17 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=402&sid=77&pid=362&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#402">Amen</a> by Emedicus <font size=2>on Friday, February 23 @ 16:07:35 EST</font><br></ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=371&sid=77&pid=335&mo